<item>
            <title>[AVRO-960] String Const Correctness in Avro-C</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-960</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I notice that avro_value_set_string() takes in a char *, not a const char *, and some of the the lower level functions it uses do take a const char *.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would presume that the library does not modify user input string data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we fix this by maintaining const char * all the way up to the user API?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
